#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.60"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.60:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.60:0.2"
msgid "6. Avijjāvagga "
msgstr "6. Ignorance "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 60. Sabbupādānapariññāsutta → sabbūpādānapariññāsuttaṃ (bj) | tathāuparipi pariññā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.60:0.3"
msgid "60. Sabbupādānapariññāsutta "
msgstr "60. The Complete Understanding of All Grasping "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.33, sc1
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.1"
msgid "“Sabbupādānapariññāya vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you the principle for the complete understanding of all grasping. "

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha. "
msgstr "Listen … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: sabbupādānapariññāya → sabbūpādānapariññāya (bj)
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.3"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sabbupādānapariññāya dhammo? "
msgstr "And what is the principle for the complete understanding of all grasping? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.4"
msgid "Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ. Tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso. "
msgstr "Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the three is contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.5"
msgid "Phassapaccayā vedanā. "
msgstr "Contact is a condition for feeling. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.6"
msgid "Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati, vedanāyapi nibbindati. "
msgstr "Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, sights, eye consciousness, eye contact, and feeling. "

#. VAR: vimokkhā → vimokkha (s1-3, km) | vimokkhaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.7"
msgid "Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimokkhā ‘pariññātaṃ me upādānan’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they are released, they understand: ‘I have completely understood grasping.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.8"
msgid "Sotañca paṭicca sadde ca uppajjati … "
msgstr "Ear consciousness arises dependent on the ear and sounds. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.9"
msgid "ghānañca paṭicca gandhe ca … "
msgstr "Nose consciousness arises dependent on the nose and smells. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.10"
msgid "jivhañca paṭicca rase ca … "
msgstr "Tongue consciousness arises dependent on the tongue and tastes. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.11"
msgid "kāyañca paṭicca phoṭṭhabbe ca … "
msgstr "Body consciousness arises dependent on the body and touches. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.12"
msgid "manañca paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ. Tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso. "
msgstr "Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts. The meeting of the three is contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.13"
msgid "Phassapaccayā vedanā. "
msgstr "Contact is a condition for feeling. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.14"
msgid "Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako manasmimpi nibbindati, dhammesupi nibbindati, manoviññāṇepi nibbindati, manosamphassepi nibbindati, vedanāyapi nibbindati. "
msgstr "Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, mind contact, and feeling. "

msgctxt "sn35.60:1.15"
msgid "Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimokkhā ‘pariññātaṃ me upādānan’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they are released, they understand: ‘I have completely understood grasping.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.16"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sabbupādānapariññāya dhammo”ti. "
msgstr "This is the principle for the complete understanding of all grasping.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.60:1.17"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

